<p>The featured people pattern allows University academics, staff, and students to be prominently included on a webpage. This is used to link to work or research profiles of noteable people affiliated with the University of St Andrews.</p>

<h3>Rules for featured people</h3>
<ul>
    <li>There must be only one featured people banner on a page.</li>
    <li>The image and name of a featured person must link to the same webpage.</li>
    <li>Linked webpages must open in the same tab.</li>
    <li>Section title must not exceed 50 characters.</li>
    <li>Featured images must be 300 Ã— 300 pixels.</li>
    <li>Featured images must be a high quality portraiture headshot of the affiliated person.</li>
    <li>It is recommended that featured people's names must not exceed 50 characters in length.</li>
    <li>It is recommended that featured people's title must not exceed 70 characters in length.</li>
    <li>The paragraph description text is optional where two or more featured people are displayed.</li>
    <li>The paragraph description text must be included when featuring only one person.</li>
    <li>Description character count must not exceed 200 characters.</li>
</ul>

